---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const phone = '01623 325 123';
const telHref = `tel:${phone.replace(/\s+/g, '')}`;

const serviceJsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Service',
  name: 'Locking Wheel Nut Removal',
  serviceType: 'Mobile Locking Wheel Nut Removal',
  provider: {
    '@type': 'LocalBusiness',
    name: 'Tyre Emergency Ltd',
    telephone: '+441623325123',
    url: 'https://tyreemergencyltd.co.uk/',
  },
  areaServed: 'Nottinghamshire, East Midlands',
  description: 'On-site removal of damaged, seized or missing-key locking wheel nuts using non-destructive extraction tools.',
  url: 'https://tyreemergencyltd.co.uk/services/locking-wheel-nut-removal/',
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Locking Wheel Nut Removal Nottinghamshire | Lost Key, Seized Nuts"
  description="Lost or damaged the locking wheel nut? Don&rsquo;t make it worse trying to DIY it &mdash; we remove damaged, seized and missing-key locking nuts on-site or at your garage. Across Nottinghamshire 24/7. Call 01623 325 123."
  jsonLd={JSON.stringify(serviceJsonLd)}
>
  <section class="service-hero" style="background-image: url('/images/locking-wheel-nut-removal.webp');">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Specialist Extraction</span>
      <h1>Locking Wheel Nut Removal</h1>
      <p class="service-intro">
        A locking wheel nut problem is one of those situations that&rsquo;s a lot more stressful than it needs to be. Most people only realise the locker is damaged or the key is missing when they&rsquo;ve already booked the car in for tyres or other work, and now suddenly nothing can happen until it&rsquo;s sorted. The good news is that&rsquo;s exactly what we do &mdash; just give us a call before you try to attack it yourself.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-call" href={telHref}>
          <span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> Call: {phone}
        </a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/#quote">Get a Quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="service-split">
        <div class="service-split-image">
          <img
            src="/images/locking-wheel-nut-removal.webp"
            alt="Close-up of a severely stripped and damaged locking wheel nut on an alloy wheel"
            width="1182"
            height="665"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="service-split-content">
          <span class="eyebrow">How we help</span>
          <h2>Call us before you make it worse</h2>
          <ul class="check-list">
            <li><strong>Don&rsquo;t try to DIY it.</strong> We get a steady stream of customers who&rsquo;ve had a go themselves and ended up making the job harder &mdash; and more expensive &mdash; than it needed to be. Phone us instead.</li>
            <li><strong>Fully mobile</strong> &mdash; we come to you at home, the workplace or the roadside. If your car&rsquo;s already stuck at a garage waiting on this, we&rsquo;ll come to the garage and unblock the job there.</li>
            <li><strong>Specialist extraction tools</strong> covering all car makes and models, designed for exactly this job &mdash; not a general workshop set.</li>
            <li><strong>Careful around your alloys</strong> &mdash; we work as cleanly as possible around the wheel face and the rest of the hub.</li>
            <li><strong>A proper replacement nut fitted</strong> &mdash; once the locker is out, a standard nut is torqued up to spec before the car moves anywhere.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-darker">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">When You Need This</span>
      <h2>The kind of situations we get called for</h2>
      <div class="scenarios">
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Booked in for tyres and the locker key is missing</h3>
          <p>Classic one. You&rsquo;ve gone to get tyres or other work done and only then realised the key isn&rsquo;t in the car. Without it, no garage will touch the wheel and the job stalls. We come out, get the locker off, and the rest of the work can carry on.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Stripped or rounded locking nut</h3>
          <p>A previous garage has put an air gun on the locker and chewed the pattern. The key now spins freely. Our extractors are made for exactly this &mdash; we&rsquo;ll have it out without scarring the alloy.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Stuck at a garage, can&rsquo;t move on</h3>
          <p>Your car&rsquo;s sitting on a ramp somewhere and the whole job is paused waiting on a locking nut. We&rsquo;ll come to the garage, get it sorted, and let them carry on.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="scenario">
          <h3>Seized lock, key intact</h3>
          <p>The key still fits but the nut won&rsquo;t move &mdash; corroded onto the stud after a few winters of salt. We can usually heat, penetrate and turn it without going to full extraction.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-light service-cta-section">
    <div class="container container-narrow text-center">
      <h2>Need a lock off?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted-dark">Pick up the phone before you reach for the breaker bar. Tell us the make, model and what&rsquo;s happened to the lock and we&rsquo;ll give you a price and an ETA on the spot.</p>
      <a class="btn btn-primary btn-call" href={telHref}>
        <span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> Call {phone}
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
